<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="239" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="5.[1452,2662,3166,3479]" pageId="5" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1458,1613,3166,3199]" pageId="5" pageNumber="239">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Bailey, 1915" authorityName="Bailey" authorityYear="1915" box="[1631,2053,3166,3199]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Thomomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="239" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sheldoni">Thomomys sheldoni Bailey, 1915</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3799834339" pageId="5" pageNumber="239">“Santa Teresa (6,800 feet altitude), Tepic, [Nayarit], Mexico.”</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[1452,2662,3166,3479]" pageId="5" pageNumber="239">
Placed into subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[1801,1982,3245,3278]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Megascapheus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="239" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Megascapheus</taxonomicName>
. Considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Richardson" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[2446,2611,3245,3278]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Thomomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="239" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="umbrinus">T. umbrinus</taxonomicName>
by E. W. Nelson and E. A. Goldman in 1934, and a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[2424,2621,3284,3317]" pageId="5" pageNumber="239">T. u. madrensis</taxonomicName>
by J. L. Patton in 2005. Resurrected to species status by V. L. Mathis and colleagues in 2013. Molecular studies show 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wied-Neuwied" authorityYear="1839" box="[1895,2034,3364,3397]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Thomomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="239" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sheldoni">T. sheldoni</taxonomicName>
to be a member of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Richardson" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[2394,2553,3364,3397]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Thomomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="239" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="umbrinus">T. umbrinus</taxonomicName>
species group, which includes 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Richardson" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[1783,1937,3402,3435]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Thomomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="239" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="umbrinus">7. umbrinus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1898" box="[1957,2120,3402,3435]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Thomomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="239" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atrovarius">T. atrovarius</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wied-Neuwied" authorityYear="1839" box="[2140,2276,3402,3435]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Thomomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="239" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sheldoni">T. sheldoni</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Mathis et al., 2013" authorityName="Mathis et al." authorityYear="2013" box="[2358,2523,3402,3435]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Thomomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="239" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nayarensis">T. nayarensis</taxonomicName>
. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
